   answer this question, I compared citizen statements and movement
   trajectories from smartphone social media communication in real-time
   with precise timestamps and locations in response to the government's
   press releases during the Kunming railway station attack in southwestern
   China in 2014. I find that while outward engagement with government
   information may increase as the government releases more information,
