Abstract = {We identify situations in which conditioning on text can address
   confounding in observational studies. We argue that a matching approach
   is particularly well-suited to this task, but existing matching methods
   are ill-equipped to handle high-dimensional text data. Our proposed
   solution is to estimate a low-dimensional summary of the text and
   condition on this summary via matching. We propose a method of text
   matching, topical inverse regression matching, that allows the analyst
