Abstract = {Political scientists increasingly use supervised machine learning to
   code multiple relevant labels from a single set of texts. The current
   ``best practice{''} of individually applying supervised machine learning
   to each label ignores information on inter-label association(s), and is
   likely to under-perform as a result. We introduce multi-label prediction
   as a solution to this problem. After reviewing the multi-label
   prediction framework, we apply it to code multiple features of (i)
