   impressions of political actors. We rely on video from the 4th
   Republican Party presidential debate held on November 10, 2016, as well
   as continuous response approval data from a live focus group (n = 311;
   36,528 reactions), to determine how the emotional displays of political
   candidates influence voter impression formation. Our results suggest
   that anger displays can positively influence viewers' real-time
   evaluations. Happiness displays, on the other hand, are much less
   effective in eliciting a response from the viewing public, while fear
   displays were rarely projected by the candidates of the debate under
