   article presents a critical-cognitive approach that is an evidence-based
   account of whether, and to what extent, English plays a role in identity
   constructions and their connection to the local politics of English.
   This approach is analytically powerful and productive not only in
   capturing the varying degrees of the contribution of the English
   language and its role but also in unraveling the ideological dimensions
   of identity and the English language. Examples of Chinese-English
   bilingual ads that are representative of the structural features of
