Abstract = {Research on the linguistic characteristics of university classroom
   discourse highlights the salience, in this register, of
   non-informational and subjective aspects of discourse. This dimension of
   classroom discourse, however, has not been studied systematically.
   Taking a corpus-based approach, this study investigates the
   non-informational dimension of classroom discourse, focusing on the
   marking of emotions, affect, and the speaker's `involvement' (Chafe
