   firms. Moreover, we find that the acquisitive nature of extraverted CEOs
   reveals itself particularly in so-called ``weaker'' situations, in which
   CEOs enjoy considerable discretion to behave in ways akin to their
   personality traits. Subsequent analyses show that extraverted CEOs are
   also more likely than other CEOs to succeed in M\&As, as reflected by
