   use validated estimates of candidate ideological positions derived from
   quantitative scaling of 7,497 Japanese-language election manifestos
   written by the near universe of candidates who competed in the eight
   House of Representatives elections held on either side of Japan's 1994
   electoral reform. Leveraging variation before and after Japan's
