Month = {JUN},
Abstract = {This study explored the effect of two planning conditions {[}the
   simultaneous use of rehearsal and careful online planning (ROP), and the
   careful online planning alone (OP)] on L2 production complexity and
   accuracy and the subsequent development of these two linguistic areas in
   the context of text-based synchronous computer-mediated communication.
   Intermediate to advanced adult ESL learners (N = 33) participated in the
   study. They completed four picture-based narrative tasks under the two
   planning conditions over a two-week period via text-chat. Two tasks were
   used as experimental tasks to gauge immediate planning effect on L2
   production and the other two as new tasks to gauge L2 development.
