   investigate how seven learners find common ground for belonging by
   telling stories as a means of active participation. The process of
   cultural belonging and participation is examined by way of narrative
   analysis-a concrete, visible, and discursive method for analyzing
   participants' daily interactions. By utilizing the dimensions of
   storytelling, which are embeddedness, tellership, and tellability (Ochs
