Abstract = {We explore the official state news agencies' digital platforms of 10
   Arab countries depict the ``Arab Spring.{''} We argue that these
   agencies serve as ``discursive propagators{''} because their outreach is
   widespread throughout the media ecosystem and are regarded as one of the
   only official sources of news on the protest movements in these
   respective countries. This article makes two main original contributions
   to the field of digital journalism. First, it introduces the theoretical
   concept of discursive propagators that addresses the often neglected
   information impact of state-run news agencies operating in authoritarian
   states and their influence on other news media. By examining this seldom
   studied area of news production in the region, we are able to glean some
