   language, particularly the -e morpheme in plural forms, in Spanish. Its
   speakers are experiencing and becoming aware of language change in real
   time concerning the use of morphosyntactic choices that seek embrace
   gender equality, diversity, representation, and diversity. This language
   change impacts directly on formal education and educational
   administrators who are under pressure not only from different social
   actors but also from their own beliefs on whether they should promote,
   ignore, or mitigate the linguistic changes that society is producing
   through their situated practices. Against this background, to what
   extent are educational authorities professionally prepared to encourage
