   how counterarguing, as the cognitive component of psychological
   reactance, influences available cognitive resources and encoding of
   message content. The results indicated that ever-vapers in the dogmatic
   PSA condition reported significantly greater freedom threats and state
   psychological reactance but not intentions to vape relative to
   ever-vapers in the suggestive PSA condition. Moreover, counterarguing
   dogmatic anti-vaping PSAs resulted in fewer available cognitive
