   female political leaders across the topics. This resulted in four
   aggregate theoretical dimensions: 1) strategic focus 2) political
   influence 3) confidence and 4) agency and communion. Our findings chart
   novel dimensions of gender bias that go beyond the widely theorized
   tension posed by agency {[}male] and communion {[}female]. These new
