   of populist communication in forced-exposure media environments.
   Responding to this discrepancy, we conducted two experiments (N = 562
   and N = 558) in which we manipulated the core idea of populist
   messages-attributing blame-in forced and selective exposure media
   environments. Our results demonstrate that citizens higher in relative
   deprivation are most likely to select populist messages. Irrespective of
