Abstract = {Does blinking function as a type of feedback in conversation? To address
   this question, we built a corpus of Dutch conversations, identified
   short and long addressee blinks during extended turns, and measured
   their occurrence relative to the end of turn constructional units
   (TCUs), the location where feedback typically occurs. Addressee blinks
