   for decades. Some researchers have focused on the effects of variously
   worded self-report measures. Others advocate the use of aggregate and/or
   behavioral data that does not rely on a person's ability to accurately
   recall exposure. Our study illustrates how an experimental design can be
   used to improve measures of exposure. In particular, we show how an
